Description: 15 handmade Nubian sherds from different vessels, Kerma Ancien? Only one rim sherd, all others are body sherds. Two of them have writing: A: 526, rim-sherd with horizontally dotted lines. B: AWS53, AW 38/39, Temple, X. Pattern of incised herring bones.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
